10/21/83  send_mail request:  append, app

Syntax:  app path


Function:  writes the printed representation of the message to the end
of an existing segment.


Arguments:
path
   is the pathname of the segment to which the message is written.  The
   suffix "mail" is added if necessary.


Notes:
If the segment identified by the path argument does not exist, the user
is queried for permission to create it.
